abstract: The first bipartisan question was whether the president would pledge that private citizens won’t be directed to conduct foreign policy without being formally designated by the administration.
snippet: The first bipartisan question was whether the president would pledge that private citizens won’t be directed to conduct foreign policy without being formally designated by the administration.
lead_paragraph: Four senators asked the first bipartisan question of President Trump’s impeachment trial, quizzing the White House legal team about whether Mr. Trump would pledge that private citizens will not be directed to conduct foreign policy without being formally designated by the president and the State Department.
headline_main: Giuliani wasn’t conducting foreign policy, White House lawyer says.

abstract: President Donald Trump lashed out at his top Democratic presidential rivals Thursday, taking his fight to the first-in-the-nation caucus state of Iowa and the crucial battleground state of Michigan.
snippet: President Donald Trump lashed out at his top Democratic presidential rivals Thursday, taking his fight to the first-in-the-nation caucus state of Iowa and the crucial battleground state of Michigan.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — President Donald Trump lashed out at his top Democratic presidential rivals Thursday, taking his fight to the first-in-the-nation caucus state of Iowa and the crucial battleground state of Michigan.
headline_main: Trump Rails Against Democratic Rivals Ahead of Iowa Caucuses
headline_print_headline: Trump Rails Against Democratic Rivals Ahead of Iowa Caucuses

lead_paragraph: One of President Trump’s lawyers argued Thursday that the president’s requests for investigations in Ukraine were not “necessarily” for investigations of former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. or his son, Hunter Biden.
headline_main: Requests for inquiries weren’t ‘necessarily’ about the Bidens, Trump lawyer says.

abstract: Alan Dershowitz delivered a stunning defense of President Donald Trump in the Senate that would essentially make it impossible to impeach a president for anything he might do to boost his reelection prospects. It was a contention quickly and forcefully denounced by a range of legal scholars and historians who said there were clear limits on presidential authority.
snippet: Alan Dershowitz delivered a stunning defense of President Donald Trump in the Senate that would essentially make it impossible to impeach a president for anything he might do to boost his reelection prospects. It was a contention quickly and force...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Alan Dershowitz delivered a stunning defense of President Donald Trump in the Senate that would essentially make it impossible to impeach a president for anything he might do to boost his reelection prospects. It was a contention quickly and forcefully denounced by a range of legal scholars and historians who said there were clear limits on presidential authority.
headline_main: Experts on Dershowitz's Impeachment Defense: Quid Pro Whoa
headline_print_headline: Experts on Dershowitz's Impeachment Defense: Quid Pro Whoa

headline_main: A question goes unanswered: Who pays Giuliani’s legal fees?

abstract: In the Senate, the president’s defense says impeachment is not a remedy to defied subpoenas. But a Justice Department lawyer says the opposite.
snippet: In the Senate, the president’s defense says impeachment is not a remedy to defied subpoenas. But a Justice Department lawyer says the opposite.
lead_paragraph: As he stood up to answer a question on Thursday, Representative Adam B. Schiff of California, the lead Democratic House manager, said that on the same day that President Trump’s lawyers were fighting his impeachment in the Senate, the president’s own Justice Department was making a contrary argument in federal court.
headline_main: Trump administration says impeachment is legitimate and not, on the same day.
byline_original: By Catie Edmondson and Patricia Mazzei

abstract: The director had said that any candidate should tell the F.B.I. if contacted by a foreign government trying to influence an election.
snippet: The director had said that any candidate should tell the F.B.I. if contacted by a foreign government trying to influence an election.
lead_paragraph: In a question, two Democrats went after the Trump legal team’s assertion that it was acceptable for the president to seek derogatory information about Joseph R. Biden Jr. from Ukraine.
headline_main: Democrats point out conflicting statements from Trump’s F.B.I. director and his defense.

abstract: President Trump has sought to distance himself from the two men, Lev Parnas and Igor Fruman, who were involved in the Ukraine pressure campaign.
snippet: President Trump has sought to distance himself from the two men, Lev Parnas and Igor Fruman, who were involved in the Ukraine pressure campaign.
lead_paragraph: A lawyer for Lev Parnas, the former associate of Rudolph W. Giuliani who has offered to testify at the impeachment trial, released a new recording on Thursday of President Trump meeting in April 2018 with a small group of donors at Mar-a-Lago, his private club in Florida.
